om/api/questions/13846/relationships/activeRevision"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"6463","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/6463"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"packs":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/6463/packs","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/6463/relationships/packs"}},"revisions":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/6463/revisions","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/6463/relationships/revisions"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"13846"},"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/6463/content","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/6463/relationships/content"}},"specialtyTags":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/6463/specialtyTags","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/6463/relationships/specialtyTags"}},"primaryTags":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/6463/primaryTags","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/6463/relationships/primaryTags"}},"contributionTypes":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/6463/contributionTypes","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/6463/relationships/contributionTypes"}},"contributors":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/6463/contributors","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/6463/relationships/contributors"}},"contribution":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/6463/contribution","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/6463/relationships/contribution"}},"myContribution":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/6463/myContribution","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/6463/relationships/myContribution"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"103619"},"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/6463/activeRevision","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/6463/relationships/activeRevision"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"11"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"1061"},{"type":"tags","id":"1087"},{"type":"tags","id":"4174"},{"type":"tags","id":"8118"},{"type":"tags","id":"10977"}],"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/6463/tags","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/6463/relationships/tags"}},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"13017"},{"type":"contributions","id":"13049"},{"type":"contributions","id":"13050"},{"type":"contributions","id":"38307"},{"type":"contributions","id":"45484"},{"type":"contributions","id":"53212"},{"type":"contributions","id":"54400"},{"type":"contributions","id":"54401"}],"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/6463/contributions","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/6463/relationships/contributions"}}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"122207","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/122207"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 36-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic with a three-month history of low-grade fever, fatigue, shortness of breath on exertion and dry cough. She reports 6 kg of unintentional weight loss over this time. She migrated from Tanzania at the age of four years. She has no significant medical history and does not take any regular medications.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, she appears cachectic. Her pulse rate is 88/min, blood pressure 118/76 mmHg, respiratory rate 18/min, SpO2 97% on room air, and temperature 37.3\u00b0C. Chest X-ray shows bilateral hilar prominence with reticulonodular opacities in the upper and middle lung zones. Interferon Gamma Release Assay is negative.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EInvestigations reveal:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHaemoglobin 102 g/L (125\u2013165)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EMean corpuscular volume 88 fL (80-100)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhite blood cell count 10.9 \u00d7 10\u2079/L (4.0-11.0)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ECreatinine 80 \u00b5mol/L (50\u2013120)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ECalcium 2.95 mmol/L (2.10-2.55)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAlbumin 32 g/L (35-50)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following complications is the patient most at risk of?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Nephrolithiasis","Chronic kidney disease","Osteoporosis","Pulmonary fibrosis","Aspergillus pneumonia"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe clinical presentation of low-grade fever, cough, weight loss, and fatigue in a middle-aged woman, along with the radiographic finding of bilateral hilar prominence with reticulonodular opacities and elevated serum calcium levels, is highly suggestive of a diagnosis of sarcoidosis. Sarcoidosis is a disease in which there is chronic granuloma formation, affecting varied organ systems. It most commonly involves the lungs and lymph nodes (mediastinal in particular), but can also affect the skin, eyes, liver, nervous system, heart, kidneys, gastrointestinal system and musculoskeletal system.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe most common complication of sarcoidosis is \u003Cstrong\u003Epulmonary fibrosis\u003C/strong\u003E, which occurs in up to 20% of patients with pulmonary disease. Sarcoidosis-associated pulmonary fibrosis develops from chronic granulomatous inflammation and fibrosis in the pulmonary interstitium. The pathophysiology remains incompletely understood, but it represents a significant cause of morbidity and mortality in sarcoidosis. Pulmonary fibrosis can subsequently lead to pulmonary hypertension and cor pulmonale, contributing to the fact that over 60% of deaths from sarcoidosis are associated with advanced cardiopulmonary disease.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENephrolithiasis\u003C/strong\u003E can occur in approximately 10% of patients with sarcoidosis as a result of hypercalciuria associated with the disease. It typically presents with renal colic pain and haematuria, which are not described in this case.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EChronic kidney disease\u003C/strong\u003E can develop from nephrocalcinosis secondary to chronic hypercalcaemia, but this is usually a late and rare complication, presenting in less than 4% of patients. Given the low incidence of chronic kidney disease associated with sarcoidosis as well as the patient\u0027s normal renal function, this is unlikely to be the most significant risk.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOsteoporosis\u003C/strong\u003E is a potential complication of long-term corticosteroid therapy used to treat sarcoidosis, rather than a direct complication of the disease itself.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EChronic pulmonary aspergillosis, such as \u003Cstrong\u003Easpergillus pneumonia\u003C/strong\u003E, can complicate fibrocystic sarcoidosis but usually presents with a productive cough and evidence of fungal infection, which is not present here. Furthermore, the incidence of chronic pulmonary aspergillosis is estimated to occur in approximately 11% of patients with sarcoidosis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOverall the mortality rate for sarcoidosis is approximately 7%. It is estimated that up to 20% of patients with sarcoidosis will develop progressive pulmonary disease, and over 60% of deaths resulting from sarcoidosis are associated with advanced cardiopulmonary disease.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Sarcoidosis is a chronic granulomatous disease commonly involving the lungs and presents with low-grade fever, cough, weight loss and bilateral hilar lymphadenopathy.","Pulmonary fibrosis is the most common complication of sarcoidosis, occurring in up to 20% of patients and can progress to pulmonary hypertension and cor pulmonale."],"references":["Jain R, Yadav D, Puranik N, Guleria R, Jin JO. Sarcoidosis: Causes, Diagnosis, Clinical Features, and Treatments. J Clin Med. 2020 Apr 10;9(4):1081. Available at: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC7230978/","Belperio JA, Fishbein MC, Abtin F, Channick J, Balasubramanian SA, Lynch Iii JP. Pulmonary sarcoidosis: A comprehensive review: Past to present. J Autoimmun. 2023 Oct 19:103107. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/37865085/","Bandyopadhyay D, Mirsaeidi MS. Sarcoidosis-associated pulmonary fibrosis: joining the dots. Eur Respir Rev. 2023 Sep 27;32(169):230085. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/37758279/","Cleveland Clinic. Sarcoidosis [Internet]. Cleveland (OH): Cleveland Clinic; [cited 2024]. Available from: https://my.clevelandclinic.org/health/diseases/11863-sarcoidosis","Nunes H, Bouvry D, Soler P, Valeyre D. Sarcoidosis. Orphanet J Rare Dis. 2007 Nov 19;2:46. Available from: https://ojrd.biomedcentral.com/articles/10.1186/1750-1172-2-46","Spagnolo P, Rossi G, Cavazza A, Bonifazi M, Paladini I, Bonella F, et al. Sarcoidosis: a multifaceted disease. Front Pharmacol. 2024 Aug 22;15:1445923. Available from: https://www.frontiersin.org/journals/pharmacology/articles/10.3389/fphar.2024.1445923/full"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"103619"},"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/122207/itemRevision","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/122207/relationships/itemRevision"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"13846"},"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/122207/question","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/122207/relationships/question"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[],"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/122207/stemMedia","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/122207/relationships/stemMedia"}},"explanationMedia":{"data":[],"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/122207/explanationMedia","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/122207/relationships/explanationMedia"}}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"103619","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/103619"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-10-23T22:30:36+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-10-23T22:33:12+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"6463"},"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/103619/item","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/103619/relationships/item"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"122207"},"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/103619/content","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/103619/relationships/content"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"11","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/11"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec1","name":"Respiratory Medicine","synonyms":["Pulmonology"],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"},"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/11/group","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/11/relationships/group"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"},"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/11/heading","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/11/relationships/heading"}},"ancestors":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/11/ancestors","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/11/relationships/ancestors"}},"parents":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/11/parents","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/11/relationships/parents"}},"children":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/11/children","self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/11/relationships/children"}},"descendants":{"links":{"related":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/11/descendants","self":"https://ap